Primary Nav Properties About Us Corporate Responsibility News Contact Investors Secondary Nav Careers Tenant Login Credit Card Payment Back to Property Listing Riverside Research Park Frederick, MD Property Overview Nestled along the banks of the scenic Monocacy River, Riverside Research Park is a world-class biomedical research and development campus in Frederick, Maryland, home to the National Cancer Institute and Frederick National Lab for Cancer Research and Charles River Labs. Co-location with the Frederick National Lab and nearby access to Fort Detrick, federal agencies, and top tier educational institutions makes Riverside Research Park the premier biotech destination in the region. Building Sizes Riverside 7: 137,500 SF Riverside 9: 417,000 SF (Riverside II - Site Plan Approved) Riverside 10: 235,000 SF Details Location 8560 Progress Drive Frederick, MD 21701 Driving Directions Contact / Leasing Brad Benna (301) 815-9964 (direct) bbenna@mataninc.com Additional Info Status: Planned Size: 1,017,000 SF / 102.50 acres Zoning: Mixed-Use Downloads Riverside Research Park Book Inquire About This Property Share This Twitter Facebook LinkedIn Email Copy Link Share Stay Connected Keep up to speed with Matan's activities by following us on social media. The Park is home to the Historic Liles Hotel, Artist Cottages, Butterfly Garden and Bandshell. Most city special events are held at this park such as Celebrate Bonita, Star Spangled Bonita, Taste of Bonita, Movies in the Park, and many more! Be sure to check out our Events Page to see what's coming up next! On the Southern... Load More Riverside Park is located in the heart of downtown Bonita Springs right off of Old 41. The Park is home to the Historic Liles Hotel, Artist Cottages, Butterfly Garden and Bandshell. Most city special events are held at this park such as Celebrate Bonita, Star Spangled Bonita, Taste of Bonita, Movies in the Park, and many more! Be sure to check out our Events Page to see what's coming up next! On the Southern portion of Riverside Park, you will find a Bandshell for live performances. A Veteran's Brick walkway and Veteran's Memorial are also placed here as a remembrance of those that have served their Country. There is ample green space for picnics, benches for relaxing, a beautiful fountain, and two picnic shelters. Parks and Recreation provides a variety of recreational opportunities for all ages and abilities and seeks to retain and improve the beauty of the City’s parks. We are always working to meet the changing needs of the community by offering new and exciting programs and events.
